<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-4">
            <h3>Apollo</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Only 1 player adds a prosperity marker</li>
                <li>All players get the $1/$4 bonus</li>
                <li>Cannot buy from creature row</li>
                <li>Cannot sacrifice heroes</li>
                <li>Cannot move Titans</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-8">
            <h3>Team Play</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Mandatory for 6-player</li>
                <li>Teammates must start on different islands</li>
                <li>Cannot:
                    <ul>
                        <li>gift gold to teammate</li>
                        <li>cross into teammate's territory (even if empty)</li>
                        <li>use teammate's fleet as a bridge</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>New goal: 3 metropolises among the team</li>
                <li>3rd metro triggers game end, even if that team loses the metro later in the round</li>
                <li>Military victory: if conquering an opponent's final territory, may immediately place a metropolis if
                    <ul>
                        <li>it does not already have a metropolis</li>
                        <li>has room for a metropolis (red square)</li>
                        <li>it would give the team a 3rd (4th, 5th, ...) metro</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<h3>Hades</h3>
<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>Start with Threat side up, Hades column at 0</li>
                <li>Before phase 2, roll 2 dice to advance column</li>
                <li>If column reaches 9, Hades enters play</li>
                <li>Hades covers the god above Apollo</li>
                <li>After Apollo, remove undead units and reset Hades</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>1 free undead, extra cost $1/2/3/4, max 5</li>
                <li>May mix & match troops / ships</li>
                <li>Moving undead is identical to Ares/Poseidon, but must include undead</li>
                <li>$2 for Necropolis, overwrites buildings</li>
                <li>Add $1 to Necropolis whenever a normal unit is killed</li>
                <li>Claim gold on Necropolis during revenue phase</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<h3>Heroes</h3>
<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>Buy from creature row, place figure on one of your islands</li>
                <li>Temples do not provide discounts and Zeus cannot discard</li>
                <li>Requires $2 maintenance, paid after revenue</li>
                <li>Never shuffled back into the deck, only retrievable with Charon</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>Worth 1 troop in combat</li>
                <li>Cannot sacrifice hero on same turn he is recruited</li>
                <li>Apollo player cannot sacrifice a hero</li>
                <li>Cannot sacrifice a hero while dying as a combat casualty</li>
                <li>Heroes may co-exist with Heroes, and may co-exist with creatures</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<br /><br /><br /><br />
<br />

<h3>Divine Favors</h3>
<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>Hades in play: shuffle <i>all</i> Divine Favor tiles, set aside</li>
                <li>Hades not in play: draw top Divine Favor for the god above Apollo</li>
                <li>Discard after action phase (whether it was used or not)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>Magic Items can be used right away or saved for later</li>
                <li>Magic Items stay face-up (exception: Hephaestus)</li>
                <li>Priestess: discard to pay a Hero or keep a creature in play</li>
                <li>Theater: "wild" building, no innate powers</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Kronos</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Free building corresponding to 1 of the Gods located above him</li>
                <li>Top position: free titan instead</li>
                <li>May spend $2 for a titan</li>
                <li>Titans: count as 1 troop</li>
                <li>May spend $1/2/3/... to move a titan on any non-Apollo turn</li>
                <li>Harpy cannot kill a titan</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Divine Artifacts</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Temples do not provide discounts and Zeus cannot discard</li>
                <li>Never shuffled back into the deck</li>
                <li>When purchased, place corresponding figure in a territory you control</li>
                <li>Artifacts can be "carried" with troops/titans</li>
                <li>Artifacts can be stolen if the territory is conquered</li>
                <li>Win <u>immediately</u> if player/team owns all 5, do not finish the round</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Special Metropolises</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>First 2 metros that are built will be these special metros</li>
                <li>Military: +3 defense (ground battles)</li>
                <li>Seaside: +3 defense (sea battles)</li>
                <li>Religious: $2 discount (= 2 temples)</li>
                <li>Cultural: new metro for 3 philosophers (mandatory)</li>
                <li>Commercial: $2 during revenue phase</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Monuments</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Place the monument in a territory after acquiring 2nd building</li>
                <li>The 2 buildings remain</li>
                <li>Does not occupy a building space</li>
                <li>Remains for entire game, can be conquered</li>
                <li>Cannot contribute to metro construction</li>
                <li>Theaters cannot contribute to monument construction</li>
                <li>Special metros and monuments can stack</li>
                <li>Buildings have no "memory"; can contribute to multiple requirements</li>
                <li>Multiple monuments can be built on the same turn</li>
                <li>Multiple monuments can be placed in the same territory</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<h3>Clarifications</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Necropolis
        <ul>
            <li>Necropolis can replace a metropolis</li>
            <li>Metropolis can be built over a Necropolis</li>
            <li>Only normal living units contribute gold: living troops/boats, not heroes</li>
            <li>May choose the order for casualties (i.e. undead vs normal)</li>
            <li>Take & move the existing Necropolis to "rebuild" one, leaving any gold behind on the board (owner of the island takes the gold at next income)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Heroes
        <ul>
            <li>if hero leaves game due to death in combat, sacrifice ability, discarded from creature row (no one purchased), or player did not pay upkeep,
then remove the card from the game. It does not go to the discard pile. Only Charon can revive them.
</li>
            <li>Exception: sacrificing Penthesilea, her card denotes the island and cannot be revived by Charon because she's not dead</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Building abilities stack</li>
    <li>Divine Favors attach to the god directly above Apollo</li>
    <li>No limit to special actions, so long as you have enough gold</li>
    <li>Reshuffle Magic Item deck if it runs out (unlikely)</li>
    <li>Mandatory to build metro if the theater can make it happen</li>
    <li>Bidding: minimum payment is $1, regardless of priests</li>
    <li>Creatures: minimum payment is $1, regardless of temples</li>
    <li>Temples: price reduction of a temple/metropolis can only be used once per round</li>
    <li>Creatures with figurines cannot co-exist</li>
    <li>Creature figurines can be placed on <i>any</i> island</li>
    <li>Chimera triggers a shuffle when it enters the discard pile by any means, and shuffles itself along with its target card</li>
</ul>
